  "coverageNotes": "Pipeline returned 50 organic keywords for mashreq.com; however relatedTerms and suggestions arrays were both empty (0 entries each, only 1 API call completed), severely limiting non-brand and topical keyword discovery. After normalization, 10 entries were removed: 7 near-duplicate merges (spelling variants 'mushreq', 'mashriq bank near me', 'mashreq bank .com'; semantic duplicates 'mashreq bank whatsapp', 'mashreq neo customer service', 'mashreq hq', 'mashreq bank hq', 'mashreq bank muraqqabat branch - full service') and 2 excluded generic non-English terms ('bank' in Malayalam and Arabic with no brand specificity). 40 unique seeds survived — below the 50–150 target due to the single-source constraint. The dataset is 97.5% brand-navigational; only 'digital banks in dubai' is non-brand. Zero problem, solution, or informational keywords were found. Major coverage gaps: no keywords for core revenue products (personal loans, home loans, car loans, savings accounts, investments, insurance, money transfers), no educational or financial literacy keywords, no competitor comparison queries, and no ICP pain-point queries (e.g., 'best savings rate uae', 'fastest loan approval dubai', 'digital wealth management uae'). These gaps align with the 8 content gaps identified in the business profile. Strongly recommend expanded keyword discovery using product-specific and service-specific seed terms to build the non-brand, informational, and commercial keyword foundation needed for content-driven organic growth."
